      "name": "CFD vs experimental hemolysis index comparison — five operating points",
      "description": "Predicted hemolysis index values from the CFD model were compared against the FDA interlaboratory experimental dataset at five flow-speed combinations. Mean absolute error across operating points was 12.4% with maximum deviation of 19.1% at the highest impeller speed. Monte Carlo uncertainty bands were computed via Latin hypercube sampling over inlet velocity, fluid viscosity, and impeller rotational speed. Experimental data sourced from the 2018 FDA study; no re-validation was conducted following the January 2026 model revision."
